<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-20T11:31:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-19T00:34:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4109: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-03-20T11:31:00-05:00" notBefore="1919-03-19T14:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received March 20, 1919, 11:31
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Following repeated from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>
                            at] Harbin.<note n="4" xml:id="d195fn4">This telegram was sent by Consul
                                General <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> while on his
                                way east for conferences at Vladivostok and Tokyo.</note></p>
                        <p>“192. March 19, 2 p.m. It is officially announced that the operations
                            against Ufa have been successful and the city was captured by Siberian
                            Army March 13. Junction point of Chishmy was also captured a little
                            later. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RPS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>